cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the standardisation of image biomarkers for high-throughput quantitative image analysis. It may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it deals with the extraction and processing of information from acquired imaging. Additionally, it could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.NE) as it involves the development of benchmark data sets and values for verifying image processing and biomarker calculations.
